steps to create a new branch locally and push it to an existing remote branch
----------------------------------------------------------------
git init
git config --global user.name "Abhinash"
git config --global user.email "your email"
git status
git add .
git commit -b "meaningful comment"
git checkout -b "your new local branch name"
git push --set-upstream origin "name of your remote branch" 
    -> before doing this create a remote branch
